This article is a transcript of remarks made by President Donald Trump during a Greek Independence Day celebration at the White House. The President expressed his admiration for the Greek people and acknowledged their contributions to the United States. He also highlighted the historical bond between Greece and the US, dating back to the fight for Greek independence in 1821. The President emphasized the importance of freedom and democracy and expressed confidence in the ability of the American people to overcome challenges and solve problems. The article concludes with the President recognizing His Eminence and thanking everyone for attending the event.